The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Friday, February 13, 2004 				 Four held for duping IISCO
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Four of the six men who had duped the Indian Iron and Steel Company (IISCO) were arrested on Wednesday during raids conducted by the detective department on charges of fraud. 																								According to deputy commissioner of police, detective department, Soumen Mitra, the six men had cheated IISCO of more than Rs 5 crore and the government of more than a lakh in the form of taxes by forging papers showing a transaction with a Bangladeshi company of 4,546 metric tonnes of pig iron and steel materials. 																								Abhijit Dey, assistant general manager, sales, IISCO, had planned the operation along with Uttam Singh, Sailesh Bajla and Krishnakumar Kejriwal. All four are in custody.
